---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Sparkline from '../components/Sparkline.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
import Sidenote from '../components/Sidenote.astro';
---

<Base title="Home">
  <article>
    <h1>Solopreneur Ops</h1>
    <p class="subtitle" style="font-size: 1.3rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-top: -1rem;">
      Agent-powered daily operations for independent educators
    </p>

    <p>
      This is a public vault — a working system that turns morning chaos into clear daily actions.
      Built by a solo AI educator in Berlin who got tired of making products
      without selling them.
    </p>

    <p>
      The core insight: <strong>action produces motivation, not the other way around</strong>.
      <Sidenote id="ba">
        From Behavioral Activation research in CBT. Martell et al. (2010) showed that
        scheduled small actions break avoidance cycles more effectively than waiting
        for motivation. Applied here to solopreneur sales.
      </Sidenote>
      Every morning, a dashboard shows exactly 5 items. One takes 5 minutes.
      One was already completed by an agent overnight. You collect the results.
    </p>

    <h2>The System</h2>

    <div class="card-grid full-width">
      <Card title="Behavioral Activation" status="active" tags={["framework", "core"]} href="/frameworks/behavioral-activation">
        <p>Action first, motivation follows. The operating model behind every daily decision.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Infinite Sales Cycle" status="active" tags={["sales", "strategy"]} href="/frameworks/infinite-sales-cycle">
        <p>Sales never stops. Every output feeds the next input. Revenue targets for Berlin 2026.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="5-Minute Wins" status="active" tags={["daily-ops"]} href="/frameworks/five-minute-wins">
        <p>The smallest action that moves the needle. Catalog of quick wins by category.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Content Leverage" status="active" tags={["content", "efficiency"]} href="/frameworks/content-leverage">
        <p>One input, seven outputs. Never create for one platform only.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Agent Operations" status="research" tags={["agents", "automation"]} href="/agents">
        <p>What agents do while you sleep. LinkedIn scout, lead research, market scans.</p>
      </Card>
    </div>

    <h2>Key Numbers</h2>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Metric</th>
          <th>Value</th>
          <th>Trend</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Monthly revenue target (Berlin)</td>
          <td>&euro;4,000&ndash;7,000</td>
          <td><Sparkline data={[3, 3.5, 4, 4.2, 5, 5.5, 6, 7]} type="area" color="#059669" /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Lab alumni</td>
          <td>350+</td>
          <td><Sparkline data={[20, 45, 80, 120, 180, 250, 300, 350]} type="area" color="#2563eb" /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Skills built</td>
          <td>50+</td>
          <td><Sparkline data={[5, 10, 15, 22, 30, 38, 45, 50]} type="bar" /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Daily action streak goal</td>
          <td>7/7 days</td>
          <td><Sparkline data={[1, 1, 0, 1, 1, 1, 0]} type="bar" color="#d97706" /></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Research</h2>

    <p>
      Deep research notes powering the system &mdash; market intelligence, competitive landscape,
      platform strategies. All generated by agents, reviewed by a human.
    </p>

    <div class="card-grid full-width">
      <Card title="Berlin Solopreneur 2026" status="research" tags={["market", "germany"]} href="/research/berlin-solopreneur">
        <p>Visa, taxes, cost of living, legal structures. The numbers behind the operation.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="AI Education Market" status="research" tags={["market", "pricing"]} href="/research/ai-education-market">
        <p>Market size, pricing benchmarks, competitive landscape for cohort-based AI training.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="LinkedIn Strategy" status="research" tags={["sales", "linkedin"]} href="/research/linkedin-strategy">
        <p>Algorithm, content types, lead generation. Weekly schedule for solo educators.</p>
      </Card>

      <Card title="Human-Agent Interaction" status="research" tags={["meta", "frameworks"]} href="/research/hai-landscape">
        <p>Frameworks, UX patterns, and anti-patterns for working with AI agents.</p>
      </Card>
    </div>

    <h2>Get Started</h2>

    <p>
      Want to build your own version? Start with the
      <a href="/start">Context Interview</a> &mdash; 10 minutes to build the personal context
      that makes agents useful. Then set up your daily dashboard.
    </p>

    <p>
      Or explore the <a href="/frameworks">frameworks</a> to understand the thinking behind the system.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
